        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer157615266" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3486955328585376638"> Breath, Eyes, Memory is an engaging story of Sophie Caco, who was abruptly summoned from her hometown of Haiti to the United States by her estranged mother. Author Edwidge Danticat introduces readers to the Caco women, who embodied strength and resiliency, but who also harbored a dark past. Set in Haiti as well as within the Haitian community in New York, this novel also addresses controversial cultural practices, and how they impact the lives of women. <br/> This was such a great book, that I was u</span>
  <span id="freeText3486955328585376638" style="display:none"> Breath, Eyes, Memory is an engaging story of Sophie Caco, who was abruptly summoned from her hometown of Haiti to the United States by her estranged mother. Author Edwidge Danticat introduces readers to the Caco women, who embodied strength and resiliency, but who also harbored a dark past. Set in Haiti as well as within the Haitian community in New York, this novel also addresses controversial cultural practices, and how they impact the lives of women. <br /> This was such a great book, that I was upset with myself that I waited so long to read it. From the first page to the very last word, I was completely enthralled by the novel, and am looking forward to reading other works by Danticat.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3486955328585376638" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

